  "text": "This report provides the first snapshot of the pragmatic effect of CR in Canada. This may help to advance the care of Canadians with CVD. Overall results suggest that revascularization and acute coronary syndrome patients are accessing CR approximately 2 months after event/procedure, that they participate in programs that are within a 30-minute \"acceptable\" [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] drive-time from their homes, and that participation results in significant improvements in risk factors and exercise capacity.",
